Oi Has Started to Buy Shares in Portugal Telecom, Diario Reports

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-03-02T08:27:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/oi-has-started-to-buy-shares-in-portugal-telecom-diario-reports.html
Brazilian phone company Oi has
started to buy shares in  Portugal Telecom SGPS SA  as it plans to
hold a stake of 10 percent in the Portuguese telecommunications
operator, Diario Economico reported, citing Otavio Azevedo, an
executive at Oi.  Oi still has less than 2 percent in Portugal Telecom, the
Portuguese newspaper said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
